  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Building on the success of neural style transfer in the image domain (Gatys et al., 2015), timbre transfer emerged as a task in musical audio synthesis.",
    "Dai et al. (2018) define timbre transfer as the task of altering \"timbre information in a meaningful way while preserving the hidden content of performance control.\"",
    "They highlight that it requires the disentanglement of timbre and performance, giving the example of replicating a trumpet performance such that it sounds like it was played on a flute while maintaining the original musical expression.",
    "Specific examples of timbre transfer using generative models include Bitton et al. (2018) and Huang et al. (2019).",
    "Timbre transfer has been explored a number of times using DDSP."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
